    <p>Two offenses of a very different nature, and by no means of equal magnitude, you last night <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="laid to my charge"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(指责我)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>…and the other, that I had, in defiance of various claims, in defiance of honor and humanity, ruined the <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="immediate prosperity"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(指日可待的富贵)</code></b>, and <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="blasted the prospects"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(葬送了前途)</code></b> of Mr. Wickham.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Willfully and wantonly to have <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="thrown off"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(抛弃)</code></b> the companion of my youth, the acknowledged favorite of my father, a young man who had scarcely any other dependence than on our patronage, and who had been brought up to expect its exertion, would be a depravity, to which the separation of two young persons, whose affection could be the growth of only a few weeks, could bear no comparison.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
